reswithian, Cornwall, Eng.":"Treswithian, Cornwall, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Bray","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of the places in Berkshire and Devon. The former is probably named with Old French <i>bray</i> ‘marsh’, the latter from the Cornish element <i>bre</i> ‘hill’.","English: perhaps a topographic name from northern Middle English <i>bra</i> ‘steep (river) bank’ or ‘brow of a hill’, denoting someone who lived at such a place.","English (of Norman origin): habitational name from any of several places in Normandy or Picardy called Bray (Eure, Calvados, Aisne, Somme); see 6."],"variants":[{"name":"Dubray","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Napoleon.","French: habitational name, with fused preposition and definite article <i>du</i> ‘from the’, for someone from any of various minor places called Bray (see   Bray  ).","Altered form of French   Dubreuil  . This surname is common among Native Americans, namely the Cheyenne River Sioux in SD."]},{"name":"Braye","meanings":["English (Sussex): from the Middle English female personal name <i>Braye</i>. Its origin is unknown but it might derive from Breton <i>bregh</i> ‘fine, brave’."]},{"name":"Brais","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Marcel, Aldea, Andre, Cecile, Fernande, Stephane.","French: altered form of   Bray  ."]}]},{"name":"Ursela","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From the Latin name <i>Ursula</i>, a diminutive of <i>ursa</i> ‘(she-)bear’. This was the name of a 4th-century saint martyred at Cologne with a number of companions, traditionally said to have been eleven thousand, but more probably just eleven, the exaggeration being due to a misreading of a diacritic mark in an early manuscript. This name was moderately popular in the 16th century, but its use in the English-speaking world today is selective. A more recent influence has been the film actress  Ursula Andress  (  b. 1936  in Switzerland)."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Ursela Bray was born about 1546, in Treswithian, Cornwall, England, United Kingdom, her father, Henry Bray, was 47 and her mother, Margery Borlase, was 36. She married Charles de La Zouche before 1580, in England. They were the parents of at least 3 daughters."},"et":{"abt. 1546–":"umbes 1546–Surnud","1535–1569":"1535–1569","1540–Male":"1540–Surnud","1546–Female":"1546–Surnud","1550–1614":"1550–1614","1554–Male":"1554–Surnud","1550–Male":"1550–Surnud","1572–Female":"1572–Surnud","1580–Female":"1580–Surnud","1581–Female":"1581–Surnud","1500–Male":"1500–Surnud","1512–1556":"1512–1556","abt. 1546":"umbes 1546","1572":"1572","1550":"1550","1581":"1581","1580":"1580","1569":"1569","1546":"1546","1535":"1535","1556":"1556","1512":"1512","1500":"1500","1554":"1554","about 1534":"umbes 1534","1540":"1540","before 1580":"enne 1580","1614":"1614","Bloxworth, Dorset, England, United Kingdom":"Bloxworth, Dorset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","Camborne, Cornwall, England":"Camborne, Cornwall, England","of Treswithian, Cornwall, Eng.":"Treswithian, Cornwall, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"abt. 1546–":"noin 1546–Kuollut","1535–1569":"1535–1569","1540–Male":"1540–Kuollut","1546–Female":"1546–Kuollut","1550–1614":"1550–1614","1554–Male":"1554–Kuollut","1550–Male":"1550–Kuollut","1572–Female":"1572–Kuollut","1580–Female":"1580–Kuollut","1581–Female":"1581–Kuollut","1500–Male":"1500–Kuollut","1512–1556":"1512–1556","abt. 1546":"noin 1546","1572":"1572","1550":"1550","1581":"1581","1580":"1580","1569":"1569","1546":"1546","1535":"1535","1556":"1556","1512":"1512","1500":"1500","1554":"1554","about 1534":"noin 1534","1540":"1540","before 1580":"ennen vuotta 1580","1614":"1614","Bloxworth, Dorset, England, United Kingdom":"Bloxworth, Dorset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England